I wanted to fly since I was little.
And today it was sort of... I flew an airplane today. I haven't quite processed that yet.
Data from Flightaware.
I'm trying to go there again next Saturday. The weather doesn't look so good right now, but it's also only Monday.
It's already becoming clear where the problems lie. It will probably be VERY difficult to get medical clearance due to the FAA's opinion on certain medications.
It's not impossible, but it will TAKE VERY long and means A LOT of extra work.
That's somewhat discouraging, but nevertheless just another problem that you have to solve. So far, it seems solvable. It just takes a lot of time and money.
If you want to know what awaits me.
The FAA is not a fan of ADHD. They definitely won't let you get medical clearance if you're taking medication for it.
